msgid "*Slide 1 - Data management - Tools*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:268
msgid "In this presentation, we are going to explore the importance of software tools that can help to maintain, clean and standardize your data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:270
msgid "Image by Mudassar Iqbal from Pixabay https://pixabay.com/illustrations/developer-programmer-technology-3461405/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:271
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide2.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 2 - Importance of data maintenance*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:276
msgid "Data Quality happens at every step in the data mobilization process. Within the roles on your team, you should ensure that someone is responsible and skilled with data maintenance and manipulation. We know that real-world data are messy and transformation and standardization is needed to make the data easily understandable and fit for use."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:278
msgid "When transforming data (for example merging columns, converting coordinates, changing datum, etc), make sure that you document changes and that you have an original copy that you can revert to if necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:285
msgid "Photo: GBIF: https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/2550021583 Anas crecca subsp. crecca Rights holder: YK License: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/ Reference: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/58969540"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:286
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide3.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:289
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 3 - What to consider when choosing a tool*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:291
msgid "As was covered in the foundations course, in the software section, in choosing tools, some things you should consider include, price, ease of use, documentation and support and any technical requirements to run the tool. No tool is perfect. The importance is to find the right balance and the tool that fits your requirement."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:298
msgid "Photo: GBIF: https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/2550075106 Asota egens confinis Rights holder: Takaaki Hattori License: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/ Reference: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/59263982"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide4.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:302
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 4 - What to consider when choosing a tool*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:304
msgid "The tools you choose may not be the tools that others use within your institution – and that’s just fine, unless your organization places mandates on the tools you can use.  You need to find and use the tools that help you to achieve the goals of your institution. So, you need to build a palette of tools that will help you and the people with whom you work to do their work as effectively as possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:311
msgid "Photo: GBIF: https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/2557763752 Crepidiastrum lanceolatum Nakai Rights holder: Takaaki Hattori License: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/ Reference: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/59465935"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:312
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide5.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 5 - Basic technical considerations*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:317
msgid "Some of the technical considerations when choosing tools should include the inputs and outputs that the tool uses for files."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:319
msgid "Does it allow for importing and exporting standardized delimited files?"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:321
msgid "Can you select encoding (for example UTF-8) when opening or saving files to avoid encoding issues with special characters."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:328
msgid "Photo: GBIF: https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/2563581359 Conus ebraeus Linnaeus, 1758 Rights holder: Robert Guralnick License: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/ Reference: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/60202919"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:329
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide6.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:332
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 6 - Tools - biodiversity data*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:334
msgid "In the Foundations course, we introduced you to a list of software tools compiled by previous trainers, mentors and students of this course. For the remainder of this presentation, we will review some of the tools that will be useful to complete the data management exercises in this course."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:341
msgid "Photo: GBIF: https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/2573970545 Chelonia mydas (Linnaeus, 1758)  Rights holder: Michael Barth License: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/ Reference: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/60577305"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:342
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide7.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:345
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 7 - Tools - text editors*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:347
msgid "When working with data files, you will often need a text editor that is able to do more than the default text editor that came with your operating system, particularly with Windows and Mac. Some good options include BBEdit, Notepad++ and Sublime. When creating files, you should be consistent and document your local settings and options. When opening and editing files, try different options and check the results to make sure there aren’t any issues before your proceed."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:354
msgid "Photo: GBIF: https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/2576413947 Microporus xanthopus (Fr.) Kuntze Rights holder: robodocjacky License: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/ Reference: https://www.inaturalist.org/photos/60705742"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:355
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide8.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:358
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 8 - Tools - taxonomic*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:360
msgid "Here we look at some useful tools for checking taxonomy within your data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:362
msgid "The GBIF Name Parser allows you to divide scientific name into its individual parts."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:364
msgid "The Global Names Resolver uses fuzzy matching to show the accepted taxon or synonym."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:366
msgid "The Catalogue of Life checklist bank offers a name matching tool. It indicates matches found within the checklist bank to the provided list of names and returns back the match along with higher taxonomy."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:368
msgid "In addition to these tools, there are tools that deal with specific taxonomic thematic categories like the iPlant Taxonomic Name Resoluton and the World Register of Marine Species."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide9.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:372
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 9 - Transforming DMS to decimal format*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:374
msgid "Often you will find within your datasets, that coordinates have been stored in the degrees minutes seconds format (otherwise known as DMS) and you will need to convert this to decimal degrees to starndarize the data for the Darwin Core fields of decimalLatitude and decimalLongitude. You can do this yourself using this mathematical formula."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:376
msgid "Decimal degrees = (minutes + arc-minutes/60 + arc-seconds/3600) * hemisphere"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:378
msgid "Hemisphere longitudinal: west = -1; east = 1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide10.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 10 - Tools - georeferencing*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:384
msgid "However, there are tools online that can help you with geoferencing and the conversion of coordinates."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:386
msgid "CRIA’s Species link hosts a variety of data cleaning tools. infoXY can help to get locality information using geographic coordinates."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:388
msgid "The Georeferencing Calculator is a tool created to aid in the georeferencing of descriptive localities such as those found in museum-based natural history collections."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:390
msgid "Additionally, you may also find Google Maps or Google Earth useful. Google Maps contains all of the navigation, mapping power and points of interest with just a small hint of satellite imagery, while Google Earth has complete 3D satellite data and just a small subset of information on places, without any point-to-point navigation."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:392
msgid "As we do not teach georeferencing in this course, it is recommended that you review the Georeferencing documentation, available on the GBIF website before completing any large scale georeferencing project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:393
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide11.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:396
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 11 - Coordinate and date conversion*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:398
msgid "Canadensys offers two tools that can help with both Coordinate and Date conversion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:399
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide12.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:402
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 12 - Command line tools*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:404
msgid "Operating systems come with their own set of command line consoles. Additionally, many desktop tools provide command line functionality to be used within those consoles. Command line tools are great for scripting to automate processes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:405
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::management-tools-Slide13.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:408
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Slide 13 - Review*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:410
msgid "Remember there are many, many sources for validating, cleaning and standardizing your data. Until you develop your preferred list of tried and trusted tools, remember to explore many options."
msgstr ""

