#.  Note the lack of empty lines between the end of the question (....) and the start of the next question
#.  (. What…) is required, so I have added // comments to help separate them.
#.  The + connects the question into the numbered list item, see https://docs.asciidoctor.org/asciidoc/latest/lists/continuation/
#.  Question 1
#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:680
msgid "Why is it best to clean your data?"
msgstr "¿Por qué es mejor limpiar sus datos?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:686
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [x] to make them as fit for use as possible\n"
"- [x] to achieve your data quality goals\n"
"- [ ] data should be cleaned by the users, not the providers\n"
msgstr "- [x] para hacerlos tan aptos para el uso (\"fit for use\") como sea posible \n"
"- [x] para lograr sus objetivos de calidad de datos\n"
"- [ ] los datos deben ser limpiados por los usuarios. no por los proveedores\n"

#.  Question 2
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:689
msgid "How should you organize your data cleaning workflow?"
msgstr "¿Cómo debe organizar su flujo de trabajo de limpieza de datos?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:695
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] work alone, you know your data best\n"
"- [x] ask your colleagues for expertise\n"
"- [x] work at an institutional level to harmonize data quality workflows\n"
msgstr "- [ ] trabajar solo, usted conoce mejor sus datos\n"
"- [x] pregunte a sus colegas experimentados\n"
"- [x] trabajar a nivel institucional para armonizar los flujos de trabajo de calidad de los datos\n"

#.  Question 3
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:698
msgid "Which is best:"
msgstr "Qué es mejor:"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:704
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [x] prevent errors from occurring\n"
"- [x] correct errors as soon as you find them in your database or spreadsheet\n"
"- [ ] not cleaning errors but documenting them as you go, so people who reuse your data know where they are\n"
msgstr "- [x] evitar que se generen errores\n"
"- [x] corregir los errores tan pronto como los encuentre en su base de datos u hoja de cálculo\n"
"- [ ] no limpiar los errores, sino documentarlos sobre la marcha, para que las personas que reutilizan sus datos sepan dónde están\n"

#.  Question 4
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:707
msgid "Whose responsibility is data quality?"
msgstr "¿Quién es responsable por la calidad de los datos?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:716
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] The person(s) who record data on the field\n"
"- [ ] The data transcribers\n"
"- [ ] The database manager\n"
"- [x] Everyone involved in the management of data\n"
"- [ ] The people who use your data\n"
"- [ ] GBIF\n"
msgstr "- [ ] La (s) persona (s) que registran los datos en el campo\n"
"- [ ] Los transcriptores de datos\n"
"- [ ] El administrador de la base de datos\n"
"- [x] Todas las personas involucradas en la gestión de datos.\n"
"- [ ] Las personas que utilizan sus datos\n"
"- [ ] GBIF\n"

#.  Question 5
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:719
msgid "Which tools can be used to clean your data ?"
msgstr "¿Qué herramientas se pueden utilizar para limpiar sus datos?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/management.adoc:726
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [x] Excel & other spreadsheets management tools\n"
"- [x] OpenRefine\n"
"- [x] Your database software\n"
"- [x] Online tools such as Scientific Names Resolver or Google Maps\n"
msgstr "- [x] Excel y otras herramientas de gestión de hojas de cálculo\n"
"- [x] OpenRefine\n"
"- [x] Su software de base de datos\n"
"- [x] Herramientas en línea como Scientific Names Resolver o Google Maps\n"

